<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-03-08T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-03-08T12:00:00-05:00" n="212" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1403: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Representative of the President</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-03-08T12:00:00-05:00">March
                                        8, 1939—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:11 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>27. Referring to the Department’s telegram No. 18, March 7, 5 p.m., I
                                immediately informed Dr. Rodríguez by telegram of my willingness to
                                consider any suggestions for changes which would make the note to
                                Honduras acceptable to his Government. I shall communicate his reply
                                to the Department.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>